The paper discusses a method for reducing the high variance problem in policy gradient methods in deep reinforcement learning. This is a topic that falls under the broad category of machine learning, specifically reinforcement learning. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of this method in high-dimensional control problems, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper discusses the extension of this method to partially observed and multi-agent tasks, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control).
